                                          TypedObject object)
        Set a TypedObject field directly into this record. Sets a field in the record as a TypedObject. This is intended to be the primary way to set fields into the record.
        Overrides:
        typedSet in class BulletRecord<TypedObject>
        Parameters:

        object - The non-null TypedObject with a valid type.
        Returns:
        This record for chaining.
        Throws:

        UnsupportedOperationException - if the TypedObject has Type.NULL or Type.UNKNOWN.

      • getRawDataMap

        protected Map<String,Serializable> getRawDataMap()
        Description copied from class: BulletRecord
        Extracts the raw data in the record as a Map. This should remain protected in child classes and should be implemented to extract the raw data stored without any extra data structures or types. This is intended to be used by BulletRecord.toUnmodifiableDataMap().
        Specified by:
        getRawDataMap in class BulletRecord<TypedObject>
        Returns:
        A Map containing the field names to the raw data for them.
